        "text": "*[Bug 18998] add Rd macro '\\linkS4methods' parallel to '\\linkS4class'*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18998>\n\nLluís (<mailto:lluis.revilla@gmail.com|lluis.revilla@gmail.com>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |lluis.revilla@gmail.com\n\n--- Comment #6 from Lluís (<mailto:lluis.revilla@gmail.com|lluis.revilla@gmail.com>) ---\nOn the patch for R there is this change on Rd.R (With some aesthetic changes\nhere):\n\n```\n        } else if((lS4c &lt;- identical(tag, \"\\\\linkS4class\")) || identical(tag,\n\"\\\\linkS4methods\")) {\n            arg &lt;- if (length(e)) as.character(e[[1L]]) else \"\"\n            typ &lt;- if (lS4c) \"class\" else \"methods\"\n```\n\nIf `tag` is either `linkS4class` **or** `linkS4methods` `lS4c` will be TRUE so\n`typ` will always be `\"class\"`. I haven't tested locally yet but that is my\nimpression from reading this change. Is this enough for setting the anchors for\nmethods?",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
